The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                            Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, Jan. 4: The stock market turned bullish today with the sensex surging 341.69 points to 20686.89 points after hitting an intra-day peak of 20762.80 points. ICICI Bank was the top gainer with a surge of about 4.7 per cent, while RIL, ONGC, Reliance Communications, DLF, L amp;T and HDFC rose between 2-4.5 per cent.                            
	 New Delhi, Jan. 4: Higher prices of some manufactured items and fuel pushed the inflation up to 3.5 per cent for the week ended December 22 compared with 3.45 per cent in the previous week.                            
	 New Delhi, Jan. 4: The government has announced streamlining of procedures to claim tax refunds under two major schemes by exporting firms which have merged between April 2002 and March 2006.                            
	 New Delhi, Jan. 4: The department of public enterprises has reminded the central public sector enterprises (CPSEs) that they can invest their surplus money only in mutual funds where the collective holding of government and its institutions exceed 50 per cent.                            
	 New Delhi, Jan. 4: The government today asked the Reserve Bank to issue bonds worth Rs 10,000 crore to suck excess liquidity from the market. The auctions will be conducted by the Reserve Bank on January 11, a finance ministry statement said.
                                                                                                                           
